If you have WSL, rviz won't work off the bat. Here's everything you need to do

Download cyclone and set it up:
- sudo apt install ros-humble-rmw-cyclonedds-cpp
- nano ~/cyclone_config.xml
<CycloneDDS>
  <Domain>
    <General>
      <Interfaces>
        <NetworkInterface name="eth0" multicast="true"/>
      </Interfaces>
    </General>
  </Domain>
</CycloneDDS>
- nano ~/.bashrc
(put at the bottom of the file)
export ROS_DOMAIN_ID=42
export LIBGL_ALWAYS_INDIRECT=0
export LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1
export RMW_IMPLEMENTATION=rmw_cyclonedds_cpp
export CYCLONEDDS_URI=~/cyclone_config.xml
- source ~/.bashrc

Then for playing the ROSBAG and listening, you need two separate terminals:
- ros2 run rviz2 rviz2 -d ./rviz_config_slam.rviz
- ros2 bag play joystick_lap_bag.db3 --clock 
    use -r 10 at the end to speed up replay 10 times bc it's kinda slow